# GEOMETRY MODEL
## Define before writing any HTML/CSS/JS.

Container:
  max-width: [value]
  min-width: 320px        ← always set, prevents mobile blowout
  padding: [desktop] / [mobile]
  box-sizing: border-box  ← always, on container and all children

For each section:
  Layout:          [single / two-column / grid]
  Height desktop:  [value]     Height mobile: [value]
  Left column:     [exact % or fr — never auto on two-column]
  Right column:    [exact % or fr — never auto on two-column]
  Overflow left:   [visible / hidden — define explicitly]
  Overflow right:  [visible / hidden — define explicitly]
  Column gap:      [value]
  Mobile collapse: [stack order @ breakpoint]
  GSAP required:   [yes / no]

---

# OVERFLOW CONTAINMENT — HORIZONTAL SCROLL PREVENTION
## Apply to every build. Non-negotiable.

**Root level (html, body):**
  html, body {
    overflow-x: hidden;
    max-width: 100%;
    box-sizing: border-box;
  }

**Every element:**
  *, *::before, *::after {
    box-sizing: border-box;
  }

**Container:**
  - max-width + margin: 0 auto — never width: 100vw (causes scrollbar overflow)
  - padding must be INSIDE max-width, not added on top of it
  - Never use calc(100% + Npx) to escape container

**Columns:**
  - Use fr units or exact % — never mix % width + px padding without box-sizing
  - Never set a column width > its grid track
  - Images inside columns: width:100%, height:auto, display:block

**Common causes of horizontal scroll — check all before delivery:**
  - Element with `width: 100vw` (use `width: 100%` instead)
  - Padding added outside box-sizing scope
  - Absolutely positioned element exceeding parent bounds
  - Translated element (transform: translateX) going off-screen
  - Grid column sum exceeding 100% (e.g. 60% + 50% + gap)
  - Inline element or image with intrinsic width wider than viewport

---

# IMPLEMENTATION RULES

**Layout:**
- Use CSS Grid for two-column: `grid-template-columns: [ratio]` — NOT flex-basis
- Grid column sum must equal 100% — always verify (left% + right% + gap = 100%)
- `min-height: 100vh` on the COLUMN — NOT the section
- Never use `width: 100vw` — always use `width: 100%`

**Centering:**
- Vertical centering: `display:flex; align-items:center` at COLUMN level
- Never center text at section level — causes drift during GSAP pin

**Images:**
- Always: `width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; max-width: 100%`
- Never let an image define column width
- Object-fit: cover only when container has explicit height

**Code standards:**
- Tailwind only — no inline styles, no CSS modules
- TypeScript only — no plain JS
- Server components default, client only when needed
- API calls via /lib/api only — never fetch in components
- Business logic in hooks, not components

**GSAP preparation (if required):**
- Before attaching ScrollTrigger, confirm:
  - No ancestor has `transform`
  - No ancestor has `overflow: hidden`
  - Left column: `position: relative` (NOT sticky)
  - Section: `position: relative`
- Mark attachment points: `<!-- GSAP: [what attaches here] -->`

