# QA CHECKLIST
## Run before every delivery.

**Structure:**
[ ] Column ratios match locked geometry
[ ] Grid column sum = 100% (left + right + gap — verify the math)
[ ] min-height on column, not section
[ ] Centering at column level, not section level
[ ] Responsive collapse at defined breakpoint
[ ] Stack order matches hard constraint

**Overflow / horizontal scroll:**
[ ] html + body have overflow-x: hidden
[ ] *, *::before, *::after have box-sizing: border-box
[ ] No element uses width: 100vw
[ ] No absolutely positioned element escapes parent bounds
[ ] No translated element (translateX) goes off-screen
[ ] All images have width:100%, max-width:100%, display:block
[ ] No horizontal overflow on desktop
[ ] No horizontal overflow on mobile (test at 320px)

**Spacing:**
[ ] Spacing consistent — no accidental whitespace
[ ] Container padding is inside max-width, not added outside

Fail any → identify the exact element causing overflow (browser devtools: outline every element), fix root cause, recheck. Do not ship.

---

# QUESTION FORMAT

Max 3 questions. Multiple choice. Structural only.
Never ask about aesthetics, vibe, or color.
Never ask and generate simultaneously.

Example:
"Before I build, I need two things:
1. Column layout: A) 50/50  B) 60/40 text  C) 40/60 image
2. Mobile: A) image above text  B) text above image"
